<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="436" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1740,2019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1740,1766]" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ren et Pang" authorityName="Ren et Pang" box="[564,856,1741,1767]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="436" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardilobus">
<emphasis box="[564,714,1741,1767]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">A. cardilobus</emphasis>
Ren et Pang
</taxonomicName>
in color pattern but can be separated from the latter by the penis with broadened, knife-shaped apex (
<figureCitation box="[708,789,1777,1803]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
) and its penis guide shorter than 1/2 length of parameres (
<figureCitation box="[160,239,1813,1840]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="437" pageId="5" pageNumber="436" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1740,2019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1848,1874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">Description.</emphasis>
TL: 
<quantity box="[402,568,1848,1875]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.56" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.52" pageId="5" pageNumber="436" unit="mm" value="1.56" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.52">1.52–1.60 mm</quantity>
, TW: 
<quantity box="[638,804,1849,1875]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1749999999999998" metricValueMax="1.21" metricValueMin="1.14" pageId="5" pageNumber="436" unit="mm" value="1.1749999999999998" valueMax="1.21" valueMin="1.14">1.14–1.21 mm</quantity>
, TH: 
<quantity box="[869,1034,1849,1875]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.95" metricValueMax="8.1" metricValueMin="7.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="436" unit="mm" value="0.795" valueMax="0.81" valueMin="0.78">0.78–0.81 mm</quantity>
, TL/TW: 1.32–1.34, EL/EW: 0.99– 1.04, PL/PW: 0.53–0.54, HW/PW: 0.67–0.68, PW/EW: 0.66–0.68.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1740,2019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">
Body oval, moderately convex, dorsum with pale yellow pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[992,1106,1921,1947]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="436">Figs 3a–c</figureCitation>
). Head, antennae and mouthparts pale yellow (
<figureCitation box="[354,434,1957,1983]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
), tip of mandibles brown. Pronotum and scutellar shield yellow. Elytra yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1311,1424,1957,1983]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="436">Figs 3a–c</figureCitation>
). Underside yellow. Legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="437">
Head with fine frontal punctures, slightly larger than eye facets, 1.0–1.5 diameters apart. Eyes densely faceted, interocular distance about 0.46 times of head width (
<figureCitation box="[737,817,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="6" pageNumber="437">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
). Pronotal punctures slightly larger than those on frons, 1.0–2.0 diameters apart. Surface of elytra with punctures much larger than those on pronotum, separated by 1.0–2.0 diameters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="437">
Abdominal postcoxal lines complete and moderately recurved, reaching about 1/2 length of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="6" pageNumber="437">Fig. 3d</figureCitation>
), area enclosed by the lines finely and sparsely punctate, irregularly distributed, broadly smooth along the lines; ventrite 1 with fine and sparse punctures at middle, uniformly distributed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="437">
Male genitalia. Penis slender, base of penis slightly broadened, apex swollen, knife-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1235,1317,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="6" pageNumber="437">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
); tegminal strut stout with membranous appendages on both sides (
<figureCitation box="[787,871,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="6" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[841,871,439,465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="437" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), penis guide stout, gradually converging apically to a tip in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[408,486,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="6" pageNumber="437">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
), longer than 1/3 length of parameres; parameres stout and elongate oval with several setae in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[390,469,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="6" pageNumber="437">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
